  nickname: lam
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jerusalem in Affliction'
      title: Jerusalem in Affliction
      number: 1
      content: How lonely sits the cityThat  was full of people!How like a widow
        is she,Who was great among the nations!The princess among the provincesHas
        become a slave!
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: She weeps bitterly in the night,Her tears are on her cheeks;Among
        all her loversShe has none to comfort her.All her friends have dealt treacherously
        with her;They have become her enemies.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Judah has gone into captivity,Under affliction and hard servitude;She
        dwells among the nations,She finds no rest;All her persecutors overtake her
        in dire straits.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: The roads to Zion mournBecause no one comes to the set feasts.All
        her gates are desolate;Her priests sigh,Her virgins are afflicted,And she
        is in bitterness.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Her adversaries have become the master,Her enemies prosper;For the
        Lord has afflicted herBecause of the multitude of her transgressions.Her
        children have gone into captivity before the enemy.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And from the daughter of ZionAll her splendor has departed.Her princes
        have become like deerThat find no pasture,That flee without strengthBefore
        the pursuer.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: In the days of her affliction and roaming,Jerusalem remembers all
        her pleasant thingsThat she had in the days of old.When her people fell into
        the hand of the enemy,With no one to help her,The adversaries saw herAnd
        mocked at her downfall.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Jerusalem has sinned gravely,Therefore she has become vile.All who
        honored her despise herBecause they have seen her nakedness;Yes, she sighs
        and turns away.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Her uncleanness is in her skirts;She did not consider her destiny;Therefore
        her collapse was awesome;She had no comforter.\u201CO Lord, behold my affliction,For
        the enemy is exalted!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The adversary has spread his handOver all her pleasant things;For
        she has seen the nations enter her sanctuary,Those whom You commandedNot
        to enter Your assembly.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "All her people sigh,They seek bread;They have given their valuables
        for food to restore life.\u201CSee, O Lord, and consider,For I am scorned.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CIs  it nothing to you, all you who pass by?Behold and seeIf
        there is any sorrow like my sorrow,Which has been brought on me,Which the
        Lord has inflictedIn the day of His fierce anger."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CFrom above He has sent fire into my bones,And it overpowered
        them;He has spread a net for my feetAnd turned me back;He has made me desolateAnd
        faint all the day."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThe yoke of my transgressions was bound;They were woven together
        by His hands,And thrust upon my neck.He made my strength fail;The Lord delivered
        me into the hands of those  whom I am not able to withstand."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThe Lord has trampled underfoot all my mighty men in my midst;He
        has called an assembly against meTo crush my young men;The Lord trampled
        as in a winepressThe virgin daughter of Judah."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CFor these things I weep;My eye, my eye overflows with water;Because
        the comforter, who should restore my life,Is far from me.My children are
        desolateBecause the enemy prevailed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Zion spreads out her hands,But no one comforts her;The Lord has commanded
        concerning JacobThat those around him become his adversaries;Jerusalem has
        become an unclean thing among them.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThe Lord is righteous,For I rebelled against His commandment.Hear
        now, all peoples,And behold my sorrow;My virgins and my young menHave gone
        into captivity."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CI called for my lovers,But they deceived me;My priests and
        my eldersBreathed their last in the city,While they sought foodTo restore
        their life."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CSee, O Lord, that I am in distress;My soul is troubled;My heart
        is overturned within me,For I have been very rebellious.Outside the sword
        bereaves,At home it  is like death."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThey have heard that I sigh,But no one comforts me.All my enemies
        have heard of my trouble;They are glad that You have done it.Bring on the
        day You have announced,That they may become like me."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CLet all their wickedness come before You,And do to them as
        You have done to meFor all my transgressions;For my sighs are many,And my
        heart is faint.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Anger with Jerusalem"
      title: "God\u2019s Anger with Jerusalem"
      number: 1
      content: How the Lord has covered the daughter of ZionWith a cloud in His anger!He
        cast down from heaven to the earthThe beauty of Israel,And did not remember
        His footstoolIn the day of His anger.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The Lord has swallowed up and has not pitiedAll the dwelling places
        of Jacob.He has thrown down in His wrathThe strongholds of the daughter of
        Judah;He has brought them down to the ground;He has profaned the kingdom
        and its princes.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: He has cut off in fierce angerEvery horn of Israel;He has drawn back
        His right handFrom before the enemy.He has blazed against Jacob like a flaming
        fireDevouring all around.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Standing like an enemy, He has bent His bow;With His right hand, like
        an adversary,He has slain all who  were pleasing to His eye;On the tent of
        the daughter of Zion,He has poured out His fury like fire.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The Lord was like an enemy.He has swallowed up Israel,He has swallowed
        up all her palaces;He has destroyed her strongholds,And has increased mourning
        and lamentationIn the daughter of Judah.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: He has done violence to His tabernacle,As  if  it  were a garden;He
        has destroyed His place of assembly;The Lord has causedThe appointed feasts
        and Sabbaths to be forgotten in Zion.In His burning indignation He has spurned
        the king and the priest.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The Lord has spurned His altar,He has abandoned His sanctuary;He has
        given up the walls of her palacesInto the hand of the enemy.They have made
        a noise in the house of the LordAs on the day of a set feast.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The Lord has purposed to destroyThe wall of the daughter of Zion.He
        has stretched out a line;He has not withdrawn His hand from destroying;Therefore
        He has caused the rampart and wall to lament;They languished together.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Her gates have sunk into the ground;He has destroyed and broken her
        bars.Her king and her princes are among the nations;The Law is no more,And
        her prophets find no vision from the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The elders of the daughter of ZionSit on the ground and keep silence;They
        throw dust on their headsAnd gird themselves with sackcloth.The virgins of
        JerusalemBow their heads to the ground.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: My eyes fail with tears,My heart is troubled;My bile is poured on
        the groundBecause of the destruction of the daughter of my people,Because
        the children and the infantsFaint in the streets of the city.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They say to their mothers,\u201CWhere is grain and wine?\u201DAs
        they swoon like the woundedIn the streets of the city,As their life is poured
        outIn their mothers\u2019 bosom."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: How shall I console you?To what shall I liken you,O daughter of Jerusalem?What
        shall I compare with you, that I may comfort you,O virgin daughter of Zion?For
        your ruin is spread wide as the sea;Who can heal you?
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Your prophets have seen for youFalse and deceptive visions;They have
        not uncovered your iniquity,To bring back your captives,But have envisioned
        for you false prophecies and delusions.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "All who pass by clap their hands at you;They hiss and shake their
        headsAt the daughter of Jerusalem:\u201CIs this the city that is called\u2018The
        perfection of beauty,The joy of the whole earth\u2019?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "All your enemies have opened their mouth against you;They hiss and
        gnash their teeth.They say, \u201CWe have swallowed her up!Surely this is
        the day we have waited for;We have found it,  we have seen it!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: The Lord has done what He purposed;He has fulfilled His wordWhich
        He commanded in days of old.He has thrown down and has not pitied,And He
        has caused an enemy to rejoice over you;He has exalted the horn of your adversaries.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Their heart cried out to the Lord,\u201CO wall of the daughter of
        Zion,Let tears run down like a river day and night;Give yourself no relief;Give
        your eyes no rest."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CArise, cry out in the night,At the beginning of the watches;Pour
        out your heart like water before the face of the Lord.Lift your hands toward
        HimFor the life of your young children,Who faint from hunger at the head
        of every street.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CSee, O Lord, and consider!To whom have You done this?Should
        the women eat their offspring,The children they have cuddled?Should the priest
        and prophet be slainIn the sanctuary of the Lord?"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CYoung and old lieOn the ground in the streets;My virgins and
        my young menHave fallen by the sword;You have slain them in the day of Your
        anger,You have slaughtered and not pitied."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CYou have invited as to a feast dayThe terrors that surround
        me.In the day of the Lord\u2019s angerThere was no refugee or survivor.Those
        whom I have borne and brought upMy enemies have destroyed.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Prophet\u2019s Anguish and Hope"
      title: "The Prophet\u2019s Anguish and Hope"
      number: 1
      content: I am the man who has seen affliction by the rod of His wrath.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: He has led me and made me walkIn darkness and not in light.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Surely He has turned His hand against meTime and time again throughout
        the day.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: He has aged my flesh and my skin,And broken my bones.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: He has besieged meAnd surrounded me with bitterness and woe.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: He has set me in dark placesLike the dead of long ago.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: He has hedged me in so that I cannot get out;He has made my chain
        heavy.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Even when I cry and shout,He shuts out my prayer.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: He has blocked my ways with hewn stone;He has made my paths crooked.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: He has  been to me a bear lying in wait,Like a lion in ambush.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: He has turned aside my ways and torn me in pieces;He has made me desolate.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: He has bent His bowAnd set me up as a target for the arrow.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: He has caused the arrows of His quiverTo pierce my loins.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I have become the ridicule of all my people\u2014Their taunting song
        all the day."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: He has filled me with bitterness,He has made me drink wormwood.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: He has also broken my teeth with gravel,And covered me with ashes.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: You have moved my soul far from peace;I have forgotten prosperity.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And I said, \u201CMy strength and my hopeHave perished from the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Remember my affliction and roaming,The wormwood and the gall.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: My soul still remembersAnd sinks within me.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: This I recall to my mind,Therefore I have hope.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Through the Lord\u2019s mercies we are not consumed,Because His compassions
        fail not."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: They  are new every morning;Great is Your faithfulness.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CThe Lord  is my portion,\u201D says my soul,\u201CTherefore
        I hope in Him!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: The Lord  is good to those who wait for Him,To the soul who seeks
        Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: It  is good that one should hope and wait quietlyFor the salvation
        of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: It  is good for a man to bearThe yoke in his youth.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Let him sit alone and keep silent,Because God has laid it on him;
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Let him put his mouth in the dust\u2014There may yet be hope."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Let him give his cheek to the one who strikes him,And be full of reproach.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: For the Lord will not cast off forever.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Though He causes grief,Yet He will show compassionAccording to the
        multitude of His mercies.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: For He does not afflict willingly,Nor grieve the children of men.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "To crush under one\u2019s feetAll the prisoners of the earth,"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: To turn aside the justice due a manBefore the face of the Most High,
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Or subvert a man in his cause\u2014The Lord does not approve."
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: Who is he who speaks and it comes to pass,When the Lord has not commanded
        it?
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: Is  it not from the mouth of the Most HighThat woe and well-being
        proceed?
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: Why should a living man complain,A man for the punishment of his sins?
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: Let us search out and examine our ways,And turn back to the Lord;
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: Let us lift our hearts and handsTo God in heaven.
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: We have transgressed and rebelled;You have not pardoned.
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: You have covered Yourself with angerAnd pursued us;You have slain
        and not pitied.
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: You have covered Yourself with a cloud,That prayer should not pass
        through.
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: You have made us an offscouring and refuseIn the midst of the peoples.
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: All our enemiesHave opened their mouths against us.
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: Fear and a snare have come upon us,Desolation and destruction.
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: My eyes overflow with rivers of waterFor the destruction of the daughter
        of my people.
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: My eyes flow and do not cease,Without interruption,
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: Till the Lord from heavenLooks down and sees.
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: My eyes bring suffering to my soulBecause of all the daughters of
        my city.
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: My enemies without causeHunted me down like a bird.
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: They silenced my life in the pitAnd threw stones at me.
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "The waters flowed over my head;I said, \u201CI am cut off!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: I called on Your name, O Lord,From the lowest pit.
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "You have heard my voice:\u201CDo not hide Your earFrom my sighing,
        from my cry for help.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "You drew near on the day I called on You,And said, \u201CDo not fear!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: O Lord, You have pleaded the case for my soul;You have redeemed my
        life.
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: O Lord, You have seen how I am wronged;Judge my case.
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: You have seen all their vengeance,All their schemes against me.
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: You have heard their reproach, O Lord,All their schemes against me,
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: The lips of my enemiesAnd their whispering against me all the day.
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: Look at their sitting down and their rising up;I am their taunting
        song.
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: Repay them, O Lord,According to the work of their hands.
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: Give them a veiled heart;Your curse be upon them!
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: In Your anger,Pursue and destroy themFrom under the heavens of the
        Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Degradation of Zion'
      title: The Degradation of Zion
      number: 1
      content: How the gold has become dim!How changed the fine gold!The stones of
        the sanctuary are scatteredAt the head of every street.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The precious sons of Zion,Valuable as fine gold,How they are regarded
        as clay pots,The work of the hands of the potter!
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Even the jackals present their breastsTo nurse their young;But the
        daughter of my people is cruel,Like ostriches in the wilderness.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: The tongue of the infant clingsTo the roof of its mouth for thirst;The
        young children ask for bread,But no one breaks it for them.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Those who ate delicaciesAre desolate in the streets;Those who were
        brought up in scarletEmbrace ash heaps.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The punishment of the iniquity of the daughter of my peopleIs greater
        than the punishment of the sin of Sodom,Which was overthrown in a moment,With
        no hand to help her!
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Her Nazirites were brighter than snowAnd whiter than milk;They were
        more ruddy in body than rubies,Like sapphire in their appearance.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Now their appearance is blacker than soot;They go unrecognized in
        the streets;Their skin clings to their bones,It has become as dry as wood.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Those slain by the sword are better offThan those who die of hunger;For
        these pine away,Stricken for  lack of the fruits of the field.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The hands of the compassionate womenHave cooked their own children;They
        became food for themIn the destruction of the daughter of my people.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The Lord has fulfilled His fury,He has poured out His fierce anger.He
        kindled a fire in Zion,And it has devoured its foundations.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The kings of the earth,And all inhabitants of the world,Would not
        have believedThat the adversary and the enemyCould enter the gates of Jerusalem\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Because of the sins of her prophetsAnd the iniquities of her priests,Who
        shed in her midstThe blood of the just.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: They wandered blind in the streets;They have defiled themselves with
        blood,So that no one would touch their garments.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "They cried out to them,\u201CGo away, unclean!Go away, go away,Do
        not touch us!\u201DWhen they fled and wandered,Those among the nations said,\u201CThey
        shall no longer dwell here.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: The face of the Lord scattered them;He no longer regards them.The 
        people do not respect the priestsNor show favor to the elders.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Still our eyes failed us,Watching vainly for our help;In our watching
        we watchedFor a nation that could not save us.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: They tracked our stepsSo that we could not walk in our streets.Our
        end was near;Our days were over,For our end had come.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Our pursuers were swifterThan the eagles of the heavens.They pursued
        us on the mountainsAnd lay in wait for us in the wilderness.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The breath of our nostrils, the anointed of the Lord,Was caught in
        their pits,Of whom we said, \u201CUnder his shadowWe shall live among the
        nations.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Rejoice and be glad, O daughter of Edom,You who dwell in the land
        of Uz!The cup shall also pass over to youAnd you shall become drunk and make
        yourself naked.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: The  punishment  of your iniquity is accomplished,O daughter of Zion;He
        will no longer send you into captivity.He will punish your iniquity,O daughter
        of Edom;He will uncover your sins!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Prayer for Restoration'
      title: A Prayer for Restoration
      number: 1
      content: Remember, O Lord, what has come upon us;Look, and behold our reproach!
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Our inheritance has been turned over to aliens,And our houses to foreigners.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: We have become orphans and waifs,Our mothers are like widows.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: We pay for the water we drink,And our wood comes at a price.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: They pursue at our heels;We labor and have no rest.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: We have given our hand to the EgyptiansAnd the Assyrians, to be satisfied
        with bread.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Our fathers sinned and  are no more,But we bear their iniquities.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Servants rule over us;There  is none to deliver us from their hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: We get our bread at  the  risk of our lives,Because of the sword in
        the wilderness.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Our skin is hot as an oven,Because of the fever of famine.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: They ravished the women in Zion,The maidens in the cities of Judah.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Princes were hung up by their hands,And elders were not respected.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Young men ground at the millstones;Boys staggered under loads  of
        wood.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: The elders have ceased gathering  at the gate,And the young men from
        their music.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: The joy of our heart has ceased;Our dance has turned into mourning.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: The crown has fallen from our head.Woe to us, for we have sinned!
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Because of this our heart is faint;Because of these things our eyes
        grow dim;
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Because of Mount Zion which is desolate,With foxes walking about on
        it.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: You, O Lord, remain forever;Your throne from generation to generation.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Why do You forget us forever,And forsake us for so long a time?
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Turn us back to You, O Lord, and we will be restored;Renew our days
        as of old,
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Unless You have utterly rejected us,And are very angry with us!
      comments: []
